                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17811205-60-off320 t17811205-60-crimeloc323"></join>, and went in to call a coachman last Tuesday, about half after four, in the afternoon; that he stood at the door, and saw two men come to the cart, one handed the hamper upon the others shoulder; his dog was left in the cart, but was eating, and did not bark; he hallowed out, got assistance, and the prisoner was taken, the man with the hamper made his escape, after the hamper was pulled off his shoulders.</p>
